title: For Sale:  300 Blackout Barrel, AR15, SBN
postcontent: This Texas Black Rifle Co (TBRCi) barrel is made from 4140 chromoly steel and undergo what is known as nitriding. The nitriding conversion is applied inside and out and offers better wear and abrasion resistance when compared to chrome lining and a phosphated finish. Chrome lining is where chrome is applied over the surface, because of this, chrome lining runs the risk of dimensional build up as well as uneven wear and loss of accuracy over the life of the barrel. Nitriding actually converts the surface rather than coating it there by offering better accuracy and no risk of dimensional build up. Perfect for building your AR15 upper receiver. title: For Sale:  ** Rare French MAS 49/56 in prestine condition!
location: 30 minutes west of Jax, Jacksonville, Florida
postcontent: French MAS 49 / 56A very nice, clean example of the scarce French MAS 49/56 semiautomatic military rifle. The production was seized after the war was over and they didn't have enough parts, time, or men to make many of these before the war ended. Making the 49/56 rifle a desirable collectors piece that was barely beat out by the M1 Garand as the military service rifle.This rifle is chambered for the 7.5 x 54mm French cartridge and includes one magazines and accessories. ( You can buy 308 and 7.62 conversion kits, but they tend to drop the price on them when they are this clean ) The parkerized finish is in 95% condition with minor wear on the moving parts and on the receiver where the magazine catch rubs. The bore is in very good condition with some wear on the rifling. Being a military surplus rifle, they do not get much better than this! The ONLY flaw in the entire gun is one of the ears that protect the front site post was broken during shipping.
